description: Alaina is CEO of Women Who Code, a nonprofit dedicated to inspiring women to excel in technology careers. Under Alaina’s leadership, WWCode has grown to serve more than 50,000 in 20 countries across 60 cities. This thriving movement offers 1,000+ free technical events, per year. In addition to her role at WWCode, Percival is an accomplished tech speaker, appearing at WSJ.d Live, NodeConf, Grace Hopper, MIT’s Venture Capital & Innovation and more. Alaina's been interviewed by Forbes, WSJ, Wired, and other publications across the globe to share her expertise on diversity best practices.
title: intervista a Alaina Percival - Codemotion Milan 2016
